<note id="Example_07_04" class="worked-example"><title>Change in <emphasis>g</emphasis></title>

<exercise id="fs-id1167064724043" class="07-ex028 unnumbered"><label/>
<problem id="fs-id1167066858880"><para id="fs-id1167066858881">The value of <emphasis>g</emphasis> on the planet Mars is 3.71 m/s<sup>2</sup>. If you have a mass of 60.0 kg on Earth, what would be your mass on Mars? What would be your weight on Mars?</para>

<note id="fs-id1167063599742">
<label/>
<title>Strategy</title>
<para id="fs-id1167067041850">Weight equals acceleration due to gravity times mass:  <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
