<title>Section Summary</title>
<list id="fs-id1167063514647" list-type="bulleted"><item>Newton’s law of universal gravitation provides a mathematical basis for gravitational force and Kepler’s laws of planetary motion.</item>
<item>Einstein’s theory of general relativity shows that gravitational fields change the path of light and warp space and time.</item>
<item>An object’s mass is constant, but its weight changes when acceleration due to gravity, <emphasis>g</emphasis>, changes.</item>
</list></section>

